---
import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Repl from '../../../../components/Repl';
import SchemeRepl from '../../../../components/SchemeRepl';
import PrevNext from "../../../../components/PrevNext.astro";
---

<Layout title="Logic Ch.4 — Logical Equivalence" favicon="🔑">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/logic/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to logic</a>

    <h1>Logical Equivalence</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Craig DeLancey &middot; A Concise Introduction to Logic, Ch. 4 &middot; <a href="https://milneopentextbooks.org/a-concise-introduction-to-logic/">CC BY-SA 4.0</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Two formulas are <strong>logically equivalent</strong> when they have the same truth value in every possible assignment. Equivalence laws let you rewrite formulas into simpler or more useful forms without changing their meaning.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- SVG: Two formulas with equals sign -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 360 80" class="w-full max-w-md" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <text x="90" y="45" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="15">&not;(P &and; Q)</text>
        <text x="180" y="45" text-anchor="middle" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="18">&equiv;</text>
        <text x="275" y="45" text-anchor="middle" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="15">&not;P &or; &not;Q</text>
        <text x="180" y="72" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="10" fill-opacity="0.35">De Morgan's Law</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <h3>De Morgan's laws</h3>
    <p>Negation distributes over conjunction and disjunction by flipping the connective. &not;(P &and; Q) &equiv; &not;P &or; &not;Q. &not;(P &or; Q) &equiv; &not;P &and; &not;Q.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; De Morgan's laws: verify by exhaustive check

(define (test-demorgan-and p q)
  ; not (P and Q) = (not P) or (not Q)
  (equal? (not (and p q))
          (or (not p) (not q))))

(define (test-demorgan-or p q)
  ; not (P or Q) = (not P) and (not Q)
  (equal? (not (or p q))
          (and (not p) (not q))))

(display "De Morgan (and) holds for all rows: ")
(display (and (test-demorgan-and #t #t)
              (test-demorgan-and #t #f)
              (test-demorgan-and #f #t)
              (test-demorgan-and #f #f))) (newline)

(display "De Morgan (or) holds for all rows: ")
(display (and (test-demorgan-or #t #t)
              (test-demorgan-or #t #f)
              (test-demorgan-or #f #t)
              (test-demorgan-or #f #f)))
`} />

    <div class="python-block my-2" style="display:none">
      <Repl client:visible initialCode={`# De Morgan's laws: exhaustive verification
from itertools import product

all_hold = True
for p, q in product([True, False], repeat=2):
    dm_and = (not (p and q)) == ((not p) or (not q))
    dm_or  = (not (p or q))  == ((not p) and (not q))
    all_hold = all_hold and dm_and and dm_or

print(f"De Morgan's laws hold for all assignments: {all_hold}")
`} />
    </div>

    <h3>Distribution</h3>
    <p>Conjunction distributes over disjunction and vice versa. P &and; (Q &or; R) &equiv; (P &and; Q) &or; (P &and; R). P &or; (Q &and; R) &equiv; (P &or; Q) &and; (P &or; R).</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Distribution laws
(define (test-dist-and p q r)
  (equal? (and p (or q r))
          (or (and p q) (and p r))))

(define (test-dist-or p q r)
  (equal? (or p (and q r))
          (and (or p q) (or p r))))

(define vals (list #t #f))
(define all-ok #t)

(for-each
  (lambda (p)
    (for-each
      (lambda (q)
        (for-each
          (lambda (r)
            (if (not (and (test-dist-and p q r)
                         (test-dist-or p q r)))
              (set! all-ok #f)))
          vals))
      vals))
  vals)

(display "Distribution laws hold for all 8 rows: ")
(display all-ok)
`} />

    <h3>Contrapositive</h3>
    <p>The contrapositive of P &rarr; Q is &not;Q &rarr; &not;P. They are logically equivalent. The converse (Q &rarr; P) and inverse (&not;P &rarr; &not;Q) are NOT equivalent to the original.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Contrapositive: P -> Q  equiv  not Q -> not P
(define (impl p q) (or (not p) q))

(define (test-contrapositive p q)
  (equal? (impl p q) (impl (not q) (not p))))

(define (test-converse p q)
  (equal? (impl p q) (impl q p)))

(display "Contrapositive holds: ")
(display (and (test-contrapositive #t #t)
              (test-contrapositive #t #f)
              (test-contrapositive #f #t)
              (test-contrapositive #f #f))) (newline)

(display "Converse holds: ")
(display (and (test-converse #t #t)
              (test-converse #t #f)
              (test-converse #f #t)
              (test-converse #f #f)))
(display " <- not equivalent!")
`} />

    <h3>Biconditional elimination and simplification</h3>
    <p>P &harr; Q &equiv; (P &rarr; Q) &and; (Q &rarr; P). The biconditional is just two implications conjoined. Other useful equivalences: double negation (&not;&not;P &equiv; P), idempotence (P &and; P &equiv; P), and absorption (P &and; (P &or; Q) &equiv; P).</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Biconditional elimination
(define (impl p q) (or (not p) q))
(define (bicond p q) (equal? p q))

(define (test-bicond-elim p q)
  (equal? (bicond p q)
          (and (impl p q) (impl q p))))

(display "Biconditional elimination holds: ")
(display (and (test-bicond-elim #t #t)
              (test-bicond-elim #t #f)
              (test-bicond-elim #f #t)
              (test-bicond-elim #f #f))) (newline)

; Double negation
(display "Double negation (not not T): ")
(display (not (not #t))) (newline)
(display "Double negation (not not F): ")
(display (not (not #f)))
`} />

    <h3>Equivalence laws reference</h3>
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-700">
            <th class="py-2 pr-4">Law</th>
            <th class="py-2">Equivalence</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-4">De Morgan</td><td class="font-mono">&not;(P &and; Q) &equiv; &not;P &or; &not;Q</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-4">De Morgan</td><td class="font-mono">&not;(P &or; Q) &equiv; &not;P &and; &not;Q</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Distribution</td><td class="font-mono">P &and; (Q &or; R) &equiv; (P &and; Q) &or; (P &and; R)</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Contrapositive</td><td class="font-mono">P &rarr; Q &equiv; &not;Q &rarr; &not;P</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Biconditional</td><td class="font-mono">P &harr; Q &equiv; (P &rarr; Q) &and; (Q &rarr; P)</td></tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800"><td class="py-2 pr-4">Double negation</td><td class="font-mono">&not;&not;P &equiv; P</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="py-2 pr-4">Absorption</td><td class="font-mono">P &and; (P &or; Q) &equiv; P</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <PrevNext prev={{ href: "/reading/logic/logic-03/", label: "Truth Tables" }} next={{ href: "/reading/logic/logic-05/", label: "Natural Deduction" }} />

  </main>
</Layout>
